                      <span>16</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-04-02</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Well, after waiting so long for this book to come back into print it turned out to be an overall disappointment. I found "Timing..." to be remedial and overpriced. True, timing itself is crucial to animation as with all acting, however this book offers nothing I didn't already learn from "Disney Animation: The Illusion of Life" or Preston Blair's How-To books, which I cut my teeth on.<BR>If you are an animator who already owns every other book on the subject and you have 30 bucks burning a hole in your pocket then this book is for you. However, if you don't own the 50 other great animation books by Frank Thomas, Ollie Johnston, Richard Williams, Eadweard Muybridge, John Canemaker, Brian LeMay, Jeff Kurtti, Preston Blair, Chuck Jones, Tony White, Culhane, Finch, Schneider, Adamson, Rebello, Green, and Hart to name a few; then please go buy one of theirs. <BR>This one is going back for a refund. Sometimes you just have to say "The Emperor is Naked."</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This book is small, but packs a big punch.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
